''[[U.S. News & World Report]]'' describes Cal Poly Pomona's admissions process as "selective".<ref name="US NEWS"/> The [[California State University|CSU system]] lists Cal Poly Pomona among 14 of its institutions with higher admission standards for first-time freshmen.<ref>{{cite web |title=Campuses That Have Higher Standards |work=[[California State University]] |url=http://www.csumentor.edu/planning/high_school/campuses_that_have_higher_standards.asp|accessdate=2008-09-14}}</ref> For the fall of 2010, out of 23,395 first-time freshmen applicants, 10,447 were admitted yielding an admissions rate of {{Nts|{{#expr:(((10447)/23395)*100)round 1}}}}%.<ref name="IRAR app. count">{{cite web |title=Application Counts by Level and Admit Type - Fall 2006 through Fall 2010 | url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~irar/stats/students/admissions/docs/Application%20Counts%20by%20Level%20and%20Admit%20Type.pdf | publisher=Institutional Research & Academic Resources at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona | format=PDF | accessdate=2011-03-26}}</ref> Of those admits, 2,019 enrolled as first time freshmen, according to the Cal Poly Pomona's Office of Institutional Research & Academic Resources (IRAR).<ref name="IRAR enrollment">{{cite web |title=Enrollment by Level and Admit Type, Fall 2000 through Fall 2010 | url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~irar/stats/students/enrollment/docs/Enrollment%20by%20Level%20and%20Admit%20Type.pdf | publisher=Institutional Research & Academic Resources at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona | format=PDF | accessdate=2011-03-26}}</ref> The average high school [[GPA]] of enrolled fall of 2010 freshman class was 3.41. The middle 50 percent range score on the [[SAT Reasoning Test]] was 950-1200(out of a possible 1600, based only on reading and math scores).<ref name="IRAR common data set">{{cite web |title=Cal Poly Pomona IRAR - Common Data Set 2010-11 | url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~irar/dataset/docs/cds2010.pdf | publisher=Institutional Research & Academic Resources at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona | format=PDF | accessdate=2011-03-26}}</ref>

Freshmen applicants who graduate high school outside Cal Poly Pomona's Tier 1 area (known as Tier 2 applicants) are rank ordered by eligibility index and granted admission based on a year-specific cutoff score.<ref name="dsa.csupomona.edu">{{cite web|url=http://dsa.csupomona.edu/admissions/ftf_impaction.asp|title=Cal Poly Pomona Admissions and Outreach - FTE Impaction|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|accessdate=2011-04-08}}</ref> Since academic year 2010-2011, Tier 1 applicants may no longer be guaranteed admissions based on the CSU Eligibility Index and may be subject to similar criteria as Tier 2 applicants.<ref name="President message - Feb 22, 2010">{{cite web |title=Monday Video <U+2013> February 22, 2010 | url=http://polycentric.csupomona.edu/news_stories/presidentmessage022210.pdf | work=polycentric | format=PDF | accessdate=2011-03-26}}</ref>

