====International Students====
Cal Poly Pomona has over 1,000 visa-bearing international students. The majority of them come from [[Asia]], but many others also come from [[Mexico]], [[Russia]], [[Morocco]], [[Germany]], and [[Zimbabwe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~international/new_students/ |title=Future International Students &#124; International Center &#124; Cal Poly Pomona |publisher=Csupomona.edu |date= |accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

===Impaction===
During the fall admissions filing period, the [[California State University|CSU system]] designates academic programs where more applications are received than can be accommodated by the campus, and designates them as "impacted".<ref>{{cite web|title=Impacted Programs|url=http://dsa.csupomona.edu/admissions/impacted_programs.asp|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|accessdate=2011-03-04}}</ref> At Cal Poly Pomona, impacted academic programs include:<ref>{{cite web|title=CAL POLY POMONA - Filing Status Notice for Freshmen|url=http://www.csumentor.edu/Filing_Status/notice_filing_status.asp?status=f&application_id=13&term_id=17702&application_type=u&application_name=Cal_Poly_Pomona|publisher=[[California State University|CSUMentor]]|accessdate=2011-03-03}}</ref>

'''[[Cal Poly Pomona College of Agriculture|College of Agriculture]]:'''
:*Animal Health Science
:*Animal Science
'''[[Cal Poly Pomona College of Engineering|College of Engineering]]:'''
:*Aerospace Engineering
:*[[Cal Poly Pomona Department of Chemical and Materials Engineering|Chemical and Materials Engineering]]
:*Civil Engineering
:*Computer Engineering
:*Electrical Engineering
:*Mechanical Engineering
'''[[Cal Poly Pomona College of Environmental Design|College of Environmental Design]]:'''
:*[[Cal Poly Pomona Architecture|Architecture]]
'''[[Cal Poly Pomona College of Science|College of Science]]:'''
:*Biology
:*Biotechnology
'''Student Support and Equity Programs'''
:*Undeclared<ref>{{cite web|title=Undeclared Students|url=http://dsa.csupomona.edu/ssep/undeclared.asp|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|accessdate=2011-03-03}}</ref>

As such, applicants are rank ordered by eligibility index regardless of local admissions area and are accepted as space permits.<ref>[http://dsa.csupomona.edu/admissions/major_impaction.asp Cal Poly Pomona Admissions and Outreach - Impaced  Majors]</ref>

Cal Poly Pomona students who wish to change majors to an impacted program must meet supplemental requirements required for that major. Requesting a change to an impacted majors must be received by the end of the initial filing period for the term for which new majors are being accepted (i.e. By February 28, 2010 for summer 2011; November 30, 2010 for fall 2011; June 30, 2011 for winter 2012; or August 31, 2011 for spring 2012).<ref>{{cite web|title=Change of Major|url=http://dsa.csupomona.edu/registrar/major_.asp|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona-Registar's Office|accessdate=2010-09-02}}</ref>

==Student life==
===Housing===
