! Spring
| <U+2022> Baseball<br><U+2022> Track & field || <U+2022> Track & field
|}

Cal Poly Pomona's most recent national championship came in [[2010 NCAA Men's Division II Basketball Tournament|2010 Division II basketball tournament]] when the university's [[Cal Poly Pomona Broncos men's basketball|men's basketball team]] defeated [[Indiana University of Pennsylvania]] 65-53 in the title game.  The Broncos are currently the most successful program in the CCAA having achieved 60 CCAA and 14 NCAA National Championships.<ref>{{cite web | title=All-Time CCAA Champions | url=http://www.goccaa.org/sports/2006/8/11/alltime_ccaa_champs.aspx | work= [[California Collegiate Athletic Association]]| accessdate=2010-04-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=History | url=http://www.broncoathletics.com/sports/2009/11/4/Traditions_page.aspx?tab=history| publisher=[[Cal Poly Pomona Broncos]]| accessdate=2011-03-31}}</ref>
