==Notable faculty and alumni==
{{Main|List of Cal Poly Pomona people}}
More than 109,000 alumni have graduated from Cal Poly Pomona over the course of its history, and over 15,000 remain active with the university through the [[Cal Poly Pomona Alumni Association]] .<ref name="Cal Poly Pomona Distinctions">{{cite web| url=http://www.dsa.csupomona.edu/visitors/Distinction.asp| title=Cal Poly Pomona One of A Kind| work=Visitor & Information Centers at California State Polytechnic University, Pomona| accessdate=2010-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~alumni/index.html|title=Alumni Affairs|publisher=[[Cal Poly Pomona Alumni Association]]|accessdate=2011-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~alumni/alassoc.html|title=Alumni Affairs|publisher=[[Cal Poly Pomona Alumni Association]]|accessdate=2011-03-04}}</ref> Some notable alumni include [[Hilda Solis]], current [[United States Secretary of Labor|U.S. Secretary of Labor]]; and [[Forest Whitaker]], [[Academy Award]]-winning actor.<ref>{{cite web | title=Resume  | url=http://solis.house.gov/biography/resume.shtml| work=Office of the Congresswoman Hilda Solis | accessdate=2008-09-20 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080730192930/http://solis.house.gov/biography/resume.shtml <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2008-07-30}}</ref><ref name="CSU Mentor">{{cite web | title=Cal Poly Pomona | url=http://www.csumentor.edu/campustour/undergraduate/1/Cal_Poly_Pomona/Cal_Poly_Pomona5.html| work= CSU Mentor | accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> [[Chi Cheng]] and [[Kim Rhode]] are Cal Poly Pomona alumni and [[Olympic Games|Olympic]] medalists.<ref name="College Prowler-Alumni & Post-Grads">{{cite web|url=http://collegeprowler.com/cal-poly-pomona/alumni--and--post--grads/ |title=Cal Poly Pomona-Alumni & Post-Grads|publisher=[[College Prowler]] |accessdate=2010-09-02}}</ref> Among other notable alumni in athletics are: [[Heisman Trophy]]-winning football player [[Glenn Davis (American football)|Glenn Davis]], former professional football player and NFL head coach [[Jim Zorn]],<ref>{{cite web | title=Glenn Davis Statistics | url=http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/D/DaviGl01.htm| work= Sports Reference LLC| accessdate=2011-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://voices.washingtonpost.com/dcsportsbog/2008/02/jim_zorn_plays_viola_and_speed.html |title=Jim Zorn Plays Viola and Speedskates |work=[[Washington Post]] |accessdate=2008-09-19}}</ref> soccer player [[Jonathan Bornstein]],<ref>{{cite web | title=Player Bio:Jonathan Bornstein | url=http://www.uclabruins.com/sports/m-soccer/mtt/bornstein_jonathan00.html|work= [[UCLA Bruins|University of California, Los Angeles athletics]]| accessdate=2010-07-20}}</ref> BMX rider [[Dave Mirra]],<ref name="College Prowler-Alumni & Post-Grads" /> and all-time [[PBA Tour]] titles leader [[Walter Ray Williams, Jr.]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pba.com/Bowlers/Bowler/11534|work=[[Professional Bowlers Association]]|title=Walter Ray Williams Jr|date=2010-03-03}}</ref>

Some notable faculty members include: [[Pritzker Prize]] laureate [[Thom Mayne]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Biography|url=http://www.pritzkerprize.com/laureates/2005/bio.html|publisher=[[Pritzker Prize|The Pritzker Architecture Prize]]|accessdate=2011-03-06}}</ref> [[Modernism|modernist]] architect [[Richard Neutra]],<ref>{{cite web|title=P&R Responses for recommendation 121|url=https://win.webdev.csupomona.edu/sppr/response.aspx?id=121|work=[[Cal Poly Pomona Architecture|Department of Architecture at Cal Poly Pomona]]|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|accessdate=2011-03-05}}</ref> poet [[Virginia Hamilton Adair]],<ref name="Cal Poly Pomona Collection">{{cite web| url=http://www.csupomona.edu/~library/specialcollections/adair/VHA.html| title=Special Collections and Archives - Virginia Hamilton Adair Collection|publisher=California State Polytechnic University, Pomona|accessdate =2010-05-05}}</ref> and [[Fulbright Program|Fulbright scholar]] [[Renford Reese]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.insidesocal.com/educationnow/2009/08/cal-poly-pomona-professor-awar.html|title=Cal Poly Pomona professor awarded Fulbright Scholar fellowship|last=Tasci|first=Canan|publisher=[[Los Angeles Newspaper Group]]| accessdate =2010-05-05}}</ref> among others.

